Group nodes should use "Fast Groups Muter (rgthree)." Synchronization principle: Setting modules are synchronized based on the colors "red/brown/green" (compatible with the old version "#4e5e4e") or the "‚öôÔ∏è" symbol. Workflow modules are synchronized based on the colors "blue/pale_blue/cyan/purple/yellow/black/default color" (compatible with the old version blue "#2b4557") or the "üìÅ" symbol. It is sufficient to match either the color or the icon. Due to ComfyUI updates, color values may change, so it is recommended to start the title with the symbols "‚öôÔ∏è" and "üìÅ."

You can copy the "‚öôÔ∏è Render Setting" and "üìÅ WorkFlows" nodes from this workflow into your own workflow and then delete the original groups.
You can also use this test workflow to build your own (recommended, as it reduces connection issues by 99%).
If you do not need to use groups to manage workflows, you can load individual workflows using ComfyUI's tabs, which will not affect the plugin's functionality.
Important Note: Due to ComfyUI's connection mechanism, if there are multiple useless connections during testing, the server may terminate the PS connection, resulting in a permanent connection failure.
